<p>A large fire tore through a multi-story shopping mall in Karachi, Pakistan, late Saturday, burning dozens of shops as firefighters worked to control the blaze. Casualty figures varied across early reports, with some outlets citing at least three deaths and about a dozen injuries, while others reported at least six killed. Officials said the cause was not immediately known, and police planned to begin an investigation after the fire was extinguished. Pakistani leaders publicly offered condolences as emergency crews continued their response.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/NhnzP954CR6oADFqqhsBzh6eMdiQ4zMmU3TDcA2EAxsB8911eYodP2rw7J2qYIUrHIpqYiDBD3CuxvYtiyiLhs_bsrDwrhLE-YXct8OcxRH5h8oojedKMY_jktuvHsYOcIgyF2XdtFAPGix7bfIzWta6d6gsfZzJ1Jjd4NlIoYeZOoWX2opFxkLKS17X2AcP' alt='Firefighters battle a blaze at a multi-story shopping mall in Karachi.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Firefighting response: Video from the scene showed crews directing water streams at the building as the fire continued to burn inside the mall.</li><li>Unclear cause: Authorities said they did not yet know what started the fire, and they would examine the site once conditions allowed.</li><li>Human toll: Reports described victims and injured people being taken for medical care after the late-night blaze.</li><li>Public condolences: National leaders’ condolence messages reflected the scale of the tragedy and the public attention on the rescue effort.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Police and investigators: Officials said the fire’s cause was not immediately known and that an investigation would begin once the blaze was put out. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/massive-fire-in-southern-pakistan-many-killed/article70521266.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>National leadership: Pakistani leaders expressed condolences while firefighters battled the blaze. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/1/18/at-least-six-killed-in-pakistan-as-fire-rips-through-karachi-shopp